  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">LUPD Disability Monitor 2016-2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This five-year project will contribute to Diakonia&apos;s theme of Human Rights. It aims at advocating and promoting the fulfillment of human rights committments.
It is based on promoting disability inclusion through mechanisms of community leadership, monitoring and information accessibility.
LUPD goal: PWDs in Lebanon enjoy their rights to inclusion and the accessibility of quality services, according to the Law 220/2000 and other relevant human right laws and regulations. Such approach should be enhanced by the promotion of the culture of transparency and accountability through the systematic practice of monitoring programs targeting quality services and rights insurance.
Project Objectives:
O1. To enhance the role of grassroots of disability groups in monitoring relevant disability policies and quality of service programing undertaken by both public and private sector toward inclusion.
&amp;nbsp;O2. The establishment of democratic grassroots disability groups with an empowered and effective self-advocacy capacity.
O3. The development of an accessible monitoring system on issues of disability inclusion and human rights.
&amp;nbsp;</narrative>
  </description>
